com.goinstant.auth

Interface User

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    PlainUser

    public interface User
    Defines properties of a User in GoInstant. For more information on users, please see the GoInstant guide on Users And Authentication.
    See PlainUser for a concrete implementation.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      Map<String,Object> getCustomClaims()
      Any additional properties about this user that should be included in the token.
      String getDisplayName()
      Display name for this user.
      String getDomain()
      The domain for this user, typically the DNS domain of your website.
      Set<Group> getGroups()
      Groups this user belongs to.
      String getID()
      Unique, permanent ID for this user.

    • Method Detail

      • getID

        String getID()
        Unique, permanent ID for this user. Numeric IDs make good permanent identifiers. Usernames and email addresses not so much, since they're liable to change.
